  "text": "Single injections of recombinant human cytokines in mice only produce a transient effect (typically 2-3 days). Repeated injections of large amounts of human cytokines are costly and labor-intensive. To overcome these difficulties, we developed hydrodynamic tail vein injection of DNA plasmids encoding cytokines in CB or fetal liver CD34 1 cellengrafted NSG mice. [CITATION_1] This simple, inexpensive and efficient method allows the expression of flexible combinations of human cytokines in vivo for a long period (2-3 weeks for most of cytokines) following a single injection. We have tested several cytokines and combinations as detailed below.",
